# React + Node.js Authentication System

The application includes user registration, login, JWT-based authentication, localStorage handling, and a protected page that displays a static table.

---

## üöÄ Features

- User Registration (Name, DOB, Email, Password)
- Secure Password Hashing with Bcrypt
- Login with Email and Password
- JWT Token Generation and Validation
- LocalStorage-based Session Management
- Protected Route (Only accessible after login)
- Static Table Display after successful login
- Logout Functionality

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack

FrontEnd: React, CSS
BackEnd: Node, Express, Mongo

---


## üñ•Ô∏è Installation Instructions

Step 1: Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/AshishProject7878/AuthTask.git
cd AuthTask

Step 2: Setup Backend

cd backend
npm install

Create a .env file in the backend folder with the following content:
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key

Start the backend server:
npm run dev

Step 3: Setup Fronend

cd ../frontend
npm install
npm start






